UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = '– Sin Fatt Choong is an Agile and Design Thinking strategist with extensive experience in software engineering, consulting, and organizational transformation. Over the past seven years, he has specialized in guiding businesses to adopt Scaled Agile practices and integrate customer-centric innovation frameworks. He is a certified Scrum Master, Product Owner, and Design Sprint Facilitator, as well as an ACTA-certified adult educator, bringing a wealth of practical expertise to his training.\n\nIn his design thinking training, Sin Fatt leverages innovative learning techniques, including LEGO Serious Play and blended learning approaches, to engage participants in hands-on problem-solving. His workshops emphasize aligning business goals with customer needs, enabling organizations to discover opportunities, prototype solutions, and deliver value effectively. With his strong facilitation and coaching skills, Sin Fatt empowers businesses to cultivate an innovation mindset and integrate design thinking into their strategic and operational processes.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta choong sin fatt' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Deric Yeak is the Founder and Director of Lefty Talents Group (www.leftygroup.com). Lefty Talents Group is a software development, design and digital marketing company that leverages on new technologies as the key driver to create compelling ideas to realize visions.\n\nHaving MNCs and established local SMEs as their clientele, Deric has experience in digital advertising and leveraging on new Infocomm Technology (ICT) to develop mobile and web applications to transform businesses to embrace the 4th Industrial Revolution (Cyber-physical Systems.\n\nPassionate in product development and teaching, Deric trains tech start-ups using Design Sprint, a problem-solving methodology from Google Ventures in accelerator programs and hackathons. He is also a regular judge for NUS post-graduate MBA courses.\n\nPrior to that, he was a trader and stockbroker in the equity market where he developed an algorithm for his own personal investments. Apart from financial services, Deric also worked in manufacturing, fast moving consumer goods as well as the offshore and marine sectors. He held engineering positions in regional sales, costing and project management.\n\nDeric is WSQ ACTA qualified Adult Educator and an alumni of Nanyang Technological University (NTU), graduating with a Bachelor of Mechanical Engineering (Honours) degree.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta deric yeak' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Dwight Nuwan Fonseka is Head of Data Science at Plano Pte. Ltd. and an ACLP-certified trainer with deep expertise in data analytics, machine learning, and AI applications. He has extensive hands-on experience developing predictive models, RShiny dashboards, and deep learning solutions using R, Python, TensorFlow, and Keras. With a strong professional background in healthcare, finance, and customer analytics, Dwight brings an applied perspective to teaching AI, focusing on both the opportunities and risks of emerging technologies.\n\nIn this program, Dwight emphasizes the principles of ethical and responsible AI, including fairness, transparency, accountability, and privacy. Drawing from his applied AI projects, he provides learners with real-world examples of algorithmic bias, data governance issues, and regulatory challenges, while offering frameworks to mitigate these risks. His teaching ensures participants not only understand the ethical foundations of AI but also develop the ability to apply responsible AI practices in organizational and industry contexts.\n\nDr. Alvin Ang: Dr. Alvin Ang is a technology and ethics researcher with extensive experience in artificial intelligence, digital governance, and educational technology. Holding a PhD in Information Systems, he has worked on projects examining the societal implications of AI adoption, algorithmic bias, and responsible data practices. Dr. Ang has designed and delivered academic and professional programs focused on ethical AI, data privacy, and human-centered design. His research and teaching promote the responsible integration of AI systems across business, education, and government contexts.\n\nIn “Fundamentals of AI Ethics and Responsible AI,” Dr. Ang explores the intersection of technology, ethics, and policy, guiding participants through frameworks for fairness, accountability, and transparency in AI systems. His sessions emphasize the ethical challenges of automation, data use, and generative AI, encouraging critical reflection on human oversight in AI decision-making. Through case studies and practical examples, he empowers learners to apply responsible AI principles that align innovation with societal well-being.\n\nTan Woei Ming: Tan Woei Ming is a data scientist and AI engineer with over 15 years of experience in applied machine learning, deep learning, and data-driven automation. With a Master’s in Intelligent Systems from the National University of Singapore and a First-Class Honours in Electrical and Electronic Engineering from Nanyang Technological University, he has led numerous AI initiatives in predictive analytics and process optimization. His work focuses on designing AI systems that are explainable, auditable, and aligned with ethical development principles.\n\nIn “Fundamentals of AI Ethics and Responsible AI,” Woei Ming brings a practitioner’s perspective to ethical AI design and implementation. His sessions cover bias mitigation, model interpretability, and governance structures for responsible AI deployment. By connecting technical understanding with ethical reasoning, he helps learners grasp how to embed accountability and transparency into machine learning pipelines to ensure trustworthy and equitable outcomes.\n\nYeo Hwee Theng: Yeo Hwee Theng is a data science leader and AI strategist with deep expertise in enterprise AI governance, responsible data use, and digital transformation. As the Data & Analytics Product Lead at Amplify Health, she drives AI adoption strategies emphasizing fairness, data privacy, and responsible decision-making. Previously, she served as an AI & Data Architect at Huawei International and Senior Data Scientist at DataRobot, deploying large-scale AI systems for global enterprises. She holds a Master of Technology in Enterprise Business Analytics from NUS and an Advanced Certificate in Learning and Performance (ACLP).\n\nIn “Fundamentals of AI Ethics and Responsible AI,” Hwee Theng teaches participants how to integrate ethical frameworks into the lifecycle of AI model development. Her sessions emphasize the importance of transparency, stakeholder accountability, and regulatory alignment in AI system design. By combining technical knowledge with governance expertise, she helps learners understand how responsible AI practices can foster trust, compliance, and long-term organizational value.\n\nTeh Siew Yee: Teh Siew Yee is a digital transformation and analytics leader with over 20 years of experience in technology, finance, and manufacturing sectors. He has held leadership roles at Standard Chartered, Hewlett-Packard, and TikTok, managing projects in AI governance, data management, and compliance. A certified ACLP trainer, he holds a Master of IT in Business (Artificial Intelligence) from Singapore Management University and a Bachelor of Engineering from NTU. His professional focus centers on balancing innovation with accountability in AI-driven organizations.\n\nIn “Fundamentals of AI Ethics and Responsible AI,” Siew Yee focuses on helping professionals understand the principles of responsible AI adoption within business contexts. His sessions cover risk assessment, governance frameworks, and the operationalization of ethical AI practices. By linking regulatory requirements with practical implementation, he equips learners to design and manage AI systems that uphold transparency, fairness, and societal responsibility.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta dwight nuwan fonseka' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Ms Eve Tan has been in 3D industry for 4 years. She is one and only Asian modulator in \nJosef Prusa facebook support team. She is also nominated for Woman in 3D Printing Singapore Ambassador in promoting event and seminar to let all women stay connected.\n \nMs Eve is a graduate ACTA trainers in Singapore IAL institute and currently conducting 3D Printing and scanning for skill future and WDA course.. She have graduate from ACC Institute of Human Services obtain Psychology Counselling, Singapore Polytechnic in CEO, she also ongoing her part-time upgrading on Moscow Institute of Physics and Technology in Post-Graduate Programs, she is keen on learning and upgrading herself during her spare time.\nShe has been doing all support and teaching to all buyer which they have purchase Prusa MK2,MK2S,MK3.\nShe also created her own 3D Home Desk Machine which is easy to fix and user friendly and with special feature of Non Break printing module in her own 3D printer in 2014.\n\nShe is proficient in :\n\nFusion 360, \nVisual Coding \nRepetier, \nMesh mixer and inksvg. \nsimplify3D\nSketchup Make\n3D Printing Skill \nGoogle Drive & GSuit\n& more…..\n\nShe love to conduct lesson in a fun and creative way to students, by example hydroponic planting systems, kitchen items, feasible stationery items and so on' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta eve tan' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Gary Chan is a Chartered Accountant (ACCA, ISCA) with over 25 years of senior leadership experience in corporate finance, regional expansion, and strategic management. Having served as Regional CFO of a multinational corporation, Director of Corporate Services for an SME, and Vice President for Asia Pacific in a Fortune 500 company, he brings a wealth of practical knowledge in financial planning, P&L management, and international business strategy. Currently the Principal Trainer and Consultant at Smart Skill Training & Consulting, Gary has delivered courses in financial literacy, corporate finance, and business management to organizations such as Singapore Polytechnic, Singapore Business Federation, and the Institute of Financial Literacy.\n\nAs an ACTA-certified trainer, Gary is passionate about equipping non-finance managers with the ability to interpret financial statements, evaluate investment opportunities, and apply financial analysis in decision-making. His training style is engaging and learner-focused, combining technical financial expertise with relatable case studies and industry insights. By bridging theory with practical applications, he empowers participants to understand financial data, improve business decisions, and contribute more effectively to their organizations’ success.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta gary chan' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Ho Kum Chuen is a Certified Master Black Belt with more than 30 years of experience in engineering, process improvement, and quality management. He has led multiple Six Sigma projects in multinational corporations, focusing on DMAIC methodology, statistical quality tools, and breakthrough process improvements. His career includes senior roles in product development, quality assurance, and customer support, where he provided consultancy on aligning operations with strategic goals and industry standards such as IATF 16949.\n\nAs an ACTA-certified trainer, Ho has delivered Lean Six Sigma training and mentored engineers in applying advanced quality methodologies. His teaching emphasizes hands-on application, enabling learners to identify waste, streamline processes, and improve workplace efficiency. With a strong track record in both consultancy and training, he ensures participants gain the practical skills to apply Lean Six Sigma tools effectively in their organizations.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta ho kum chuen' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Janice Ong is an experienced marketing strategist, business development professional, and WSQ-certified ACLP trainer with over 20 years of experience across IT, engineering, and e-commerce sectors. Having led regional marketing and sales operations for Creative Technology, Asco Freight, and Condat, she has a strong foundation in digital strategy, brand communications, and international business expansion. As a freelance digital marketing consultant and trainer since 2014, she has mentored professionals and business owners in SEO, SEM, and online brand development across multiple CMS and e-commerce platforms such as Shopify and WooCommerce.\n\nIn “Create Engaging Social E-Commerce Campaigns on XiaoHongShu,” Janice guides participants through the end-to-end process of building compelling brand narratives and optimizing social selling strategies. Her lessons focus on content marketing, platform analytics, and influencer collaboration—empowering learners to create authentic and high-performing XiaoHongShu campaigns that resonate with China’s digitally savvy consumer base.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta janice ong' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Jyoti Chopra is an experienced AutoCAD instructor and design professional with extensive expertise in architectural design, furniture design, simulation, and 3D visualization. She has worked on projects involving technical drawing, space planning, and digital prototyping, helping learners and organizations develop skills in design documentation and visualization. Her teaching is grounded in industry-relevant experience, ensuring participants acquire both creativity and technical proficiency.\n\nAs a trainer, Jyoti has taught WSQ and professional courses in AutoCAD, graphic design, and 3D modeling, emphasizing practical application and portfolio-ready outputs. She leverages real-world case studies and design projects to help learners master AutoCAD tools and apply them to diverse industries. Her facilitation style encourages creativity, precision, and efficiency, enabling participants to confidently use design software for both academic and professional growth.\n\nDr. Alfred Ang: Dr. Alfred Ang is a distinguished technology educator, researcher, and entrepreneur with more than 25 years of experience across IT, AI, and software development. He holds a PhD in Electrical Engineering from the National University of Singapore, an MEng from NTU, and an MBA from Universitas 21 Global. As the Founder and Managing Director of Tertiary Infotech Pte. Ltd., Dr. Ang has led the design and development of over 130 WSQ- and IBF-accredited courses spanning data analytics, cloud computing, and digital transformation. His technical background includes software engineering, programming, and emerging technologies such as extended reality (XR) and AI for creative industries.\n\nIn the Fast-Track to Unreal Game Development course, Dr. Ang combines his expertise in software architecture and technical education to provide learners with a strong foundation in Unreal Engine and interactive media systems. His sessions emphasize structured development workflows, coding fundamentals, and creative problem-solving techniques essential to modern game production. Through his guidance, participants gain both the technical competence and strategic mindset to succeed in the fast-evolving field of game design and development.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta jyoti chopra' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Ken Hiong is a ACTA certified trainer. Ken has over 20 years of work experience in the healthcare and pharmaceutical industry, having assumed various functional and managerial roles in sales, marketing, business development, finance, business analysis and planning. With an interest and experience in scripting, Ken has worked on projects using HTML, CSS, PHP, MySQL, WordPress, MS Office, VBA, Power BI, etc. Notably, Ken is a proven expert Excel user at work who has made efficient many work processes, improved data analysis and enhanced the quality of business planning and reporting for organizations.\n\nKen graduated with a Pharmacy degree, holds a Master of Business Administration from the National University of Singapore and a Master of Applied Finance from the University of Adelaide. An ardent advocate of lifelong learning, Ken is ACTA trained and seeks to continually upgrade his IT skills through various channels of learning and Microsoft certifications. With MS Office Master qualification, Ken looks forward to assisting individuals and corporations improve their computer skills, productivity and business outcomes.\n\n ' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta ken hiong' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = '– Ken Yuen is an ACTA-certified adult educator specializing in STEM education, IoT systems, and programming. With a background in electrical and electronics engineering from NTU, he has conducted WSQ and SkillsFuture courses in Arduino, Raspberry Pi, micro:bit, Jetson Nano, and Python. He is also a registered MOE instructor, having taught coding and robotics programs in over 50 schools, equipping students and professionals alike with practical IoT and programming skills.\n\nIn his IoT courses, Ken focuses on hands-on experimentation with microcontrollers, sensors, and automation systems. His prior experience as a Technical Consultant at Anson Engineering saw him develop IoT-based SCADA and temperature monitoring systems for industrial applications, giving him strong industry insight. By blending educational expertise with technical project experience, Ken ensures learners develop the confidence to build, test, and apply IoT solutions in real-world contexts.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta ken yuen' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Khoo Yong is an ACTA-certified trainer with a strong foundation in adult education and applied analytics. With years of experience in training and mentoring learners, he specializes in simplifying complex concepts in data analysis and statistical methods for beginners. His expertise includes guiding participants in applying R programming to perform descriptive statistics, hypothesis testing, and data visualization, equipping them with practical skills to analyze data effectively and interpret results with confidence.\n\nAs a certified adult educator, Khoo Yong ensures his training is engaging, structured, and accessible to learners from diverse backgrounds. He emphasizes hands-on practice with R, enabling participants to bridge theory with application in real-world contexts. His learner-centered approach not only builds technical competency but also fosters analytical thinking, preparing participants to use statistical tools in business, research, and decision-making.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta khoo yong' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = '– Lim Cheng Chong is an ACTA-certified trainer and NUS Computer Science graduate with a focus on education and interactive media. He has over 5 years of classroom teaching experience at institutions such as BCA Academy and NUS, in addition to creating more than 900 educational videos with over 5 million views on his YouTube channel. His expertise includes web programming, app development, IoT, and applied machine learning, supported by professional training engagements with CSIT, SMRT, Panasonic, HP, and other organizations.\n\nIn his React training, Cheng Chong leverages his extensive teaching and content creation experience to simplify complex coding concepts for beginners. His sessions emphasize hands-on learning, guiding participants through building functional React applications while reinforcing programming fundamentals. With his proven track record in both education and real-world projects, he equips learners to confidently develop and deploy their first web apps using React.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta lim cheng chong' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Lynn Foo specialises in Sustainability & ESG, Carbon Footprint Measurement & Management, ESG Reporting & Disclosure, Circular Economy/Waste Management. As a certified Sustainability (ESG) Practitioner by the Centre for Sustainability and Excellence (CSE), Lynn serves as the principal trainer for the HP-SIM SkillsFuture Queen Bee Programme - Advancing Towards a Sustainable Industry 4.0. She also imparts her knowledge to various Institutes of Higher Learning and SSG approved training partners. Leveraging her expertise in design thinking, Lynn coaches professionals in utilizing Design Thinking framework and circular economy business models to develop sustainable products and services. \n\nAs a business practitioner with over 20 years of industry experience, including a tenure as the Director of an international school, Lynn spearheaded various portfolios including corporate strategy, sustainability initiatives, corporate social responsibility programmes and regulatory compliance.\n\nLynn holds the Advanced Certificate in Integrating Sustainability for a Future-Ready Business (SMU). In addition to being a CSE certified Sustainability (ESG) Practitioner, she is a Lead Auditor for ISO 14001, an accredited Green Mark Associate (Singapore Green Building Council), an IBM certified Design Thinking Instructor, a certified Scrum Master, an IAPP certified Information Privacy Manager, and an IMDA approved PDPA trainer.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta lynn foo' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Noel Lou is an experienced embedded systems engineer and educator with over 15 years of expertise in C programming, IoT development, and robotics integration. He has designed and implemented numerous automation projects using Arduino, Raspberry Pi, and ESP32 platforms for both industrial and educational applications. As an ACLP-certified trainer, Noel is known for his ability to simplify complex programming and hardware integration concepts, making them accessible to learners from diverse technical backgrounds. His passion for teaching lies in bridging electronics, coding, and AI-assisted design to foster innovation and creativity.\n\nIn “AI-Assisted C Programming for Arduino,” Noel teaches participants how to leverage generative AI tools to accelerate embedded software development and hardware prototyping. His sessions focus on AI-guided code generation, debugging, and optimization techniques to streamline C programming workflows. Through hands-on exercises involving real-world Arduino projects, he equips learners with the skills to design intelligent systems that blend classical programming with modern AI-driven development approaches.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta noel lou' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = '- Patrick Foo is an ACTA-certified trainer with extensive experience in digital marketing, specializing in Search Engine Optimization (SEO) strategies that drive measurable business results. With a strong background in adult education and a proven ability to simplify complex digital concepts, Patrick has empowered learners from diverse industries to adopt effective SEO techniques for improving online visibility. His expertise spans keyword research, content optimization, website analytics, and technical SEO, enabling participants to enhance brand awareness and strengthen their digital presence.\n\nIn addition to his training credentials, Patrick brings practical industry insights gained from supporting organizations in optimizing their digital marketing campaigns. He has guided businesses to improve search rankings, increase organic traffic, and convert online engagement into tangible growth. Learners attending his sessions benefit from hands-on exercises, real-world case studies, and actionable strategies tailored to Singapore’s business landscape. With his engaging and practical teaching style, Patrick ensures participants leave equipped to leverage SEO as a powerful tool for boosting online business success.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta patrick foo' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Peter Goh brings over two decades of IT and software development expertise, with a career spanning technology evangelism, project management, and consulting in both enterprise and consumer applications. His extensive project portfolio includes developing and maintaining large-scale mobile and e-commerce solutions for organizations such as Resorts World Sentosa, People’s Association, Fancl Singapore, and NTUC FairPrice. With a strong foundation in Microsoft server technologies, SQL databases, and development environments like Visual Studio, he possesses deep knowledge of system integration and application deployment.\n\nAs a trainer, Peter has conducted courses in iOS Programming, AWS Cloud Services, AngularJS, and Node.js, consistently bridging advanced technical concepts with practical, hands-on learning. His ability to align business needs with robust technical solutions makes him an effective guide for learners seeking to master Power Apps and Power Automate. By combining his rich industry experience with a clear teaching methodology, Peter ensures that participants gain the confidence to design, integrate, and automate applications that support organizational transformation.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta peter goh' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Sanjiv i is an ACTA certified experienced leader with a proven track record in business / finance consulting and in developing i) business intelligence (BI) solutions ii) data analytics/analysis solutions and iii) IOT lead BI solutions. Sanjiv\'s goal through Prudentia Consulting, is to promote the simple joy and excitement of actively using the Microsoft Platform. He believes that the agility afforded by the Microsoft platform helps businesses get time back for deeper business thinking and to spend more time with their end customers\n\nSanjiv has rich experiences in diverse/complex high-tech businesses, turn around environments and strategic transformations. His functional expertise is in sales analytics, financial planning and analysis, engineering and program management. He has worked across discrete manufacturing, professional services and higher education verticals. He also has a working knowledge of equities portfolio management within the financial services domain.Sanjiv is the CEO of Prudentia Consulting, an organization committed to promoting the active usage of the Microsoft Platform. Prior to this, he has worked at Microsoft (US & APAC: 9.2 years), Cognizant Tech Solutions (3.3 years), Yazaki North America (8 years) and until recently at Oracle. Here are a few of his BI/analytics projects driven at scale: Built APAC wide BI dashboard using the Power BI umbrella tool set (Power BI online, Power BI desktop and Power Pivot) and a KPI lake (SQL DB), Helped develop key KPIs – identified key KPIs and helped land this in the DB, Developed a budget audit tool that captured budget inputs from a host of countries across the globe, Developed a business unit P&L reporting tool (functional architecture) in Business Objects for the world-wide financial planning and analysis team.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta sanjiv venkatram' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Shanique Moh Pei Lan is an accomplished visual communication and digital media professional with over a decade of experience in design, animation, and creative arts education. She holds a WSQ Diploma in 3D Animation and Digital Art, a Certificate in UX/UI from LASALLE College of the Arts, and multiple WSQ certifications in design, typography, and Adobe tools. Proficient in industry-standard software such as Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign, After Effects, and Premiere Pro, Shanique has applied her expertise as a 2D artist, graphic designer, and art instructor across diverse creative industries. Her career includes work in game design, medical aesthetics, and freelance visual projects, where she developed digital assets, branding collaterals, and creative environments that merge technical skills with artistic vision\n\nAs a WSQ-certified ACTA trainer, Shanique has conducted courses at Tertiary Infotech, First Media Academy, and Music Factory Academy, training adult learners in Adobe Creative Suite, design fundamentals, and digital photography. She is passionate about equipping learners with both foundational design principles and emerging AI-powered creative tools to unlock new forms of visual storytelling. Her teaching style emphasizes patience, clarity, and practical application, ensuring learners can confidently create impactful visual art that blends traditional design with cutting-edge AI technologies. With her strong background in both creative practice and adult training, Shanique is well positioned to guide participants in leveraging AI to produce stunning, professional-grade visual art.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta shanique moh' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Shawn Koh Boon Hiap is a ACTA certified trainer and used to be a specialist trainer in RSAF training specialists and officers. He was also invited by Prime Minister Office on Dec 2019 as guest speaker for Smart Nation event held in Downtown East. Throughout his career in the corporate world, he was also coach and mentor to many others, often relinquishing his leadership to take on more challenging tasks after imparting his knowledge and skillsets to his successors. Shawn is skilled in IoT integrations and development, network administration, system administration, website development, software development, multimedia production, information security, entrepreneurship, corporate leadership and project management.\n\nHe is a corporate leader and turned as entrepreneur, is the founder of I.O.T. Workz, a Smart Nation ambassador, offering integrated IoT solutions for residential, commercial and industrial. He was a self-learned programmer and won the National Software Competition North Zone Champion in 1990. He developed the first predictive online-data reduction system in 1996 for the Command and Control (C2) Center in RSAF to provide real-time system health monitoring in the data center. He also formed the Ground-Based Radar System team in ST Electronics (InfoSoft) to provide software maintenance for all radar systems in Singapore between 2003 and 2006. He was also the solution architect for multiple generations of Derivatives Clearing Systems, Head of Enterprise Solutions and held a couple of other leadership roles in SGX between 2007 and 2018. Throughout his years of exposure with Technology, he had mastered many different programming languages, acquired electronics troubleshooting skills and earn professional certifications in PMP, Information Security, Linux Administration and many others.\n\n ' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta shawn koh' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Stephen Tan is an operations and supply chain management professional with more than 20 years of leadership experience in global organizations, including Symrise, Dragoco, and Hewlett-Packard. His expertise includes managing large-scale projects, leading cross-functional teams, and implementing process improvements across multiple countries. Certified as a ScrumMaster (CSM) and Scrum Product Owner (CSPO), Stephen has applied agile principles to streamline IT-enabled business processes and enhance organizational performance.\n\nWith an MBA in General Management and certifications in leadership and negotiation, Stephen brings both strategic and operational perspectives into agile project management. As a trainer, he emphasizes the integration of agile methodologies into IT projects, focusing on stakeholder management, iterative delivery, and value-driven outcomes. His ability to bridge business strategy with agile execution equips learners with the skills to lead IT projects effectively in today’s fast-paced digital landscape.\n\nChoong Sin Fatt: Choong Sin Fatt is a senior project management professional and IT consultant with more than 20 years of experience leading software development, system integration, and digital transformation projects. He is a certified PMP and Scrum Master, known for his ability to combine structured methodologies with agile innovation. Throughout his career, he has helped organizations implement hybrid project management frameworks that balance predictability with flexibility, ensuring successful delivery across complex technical initiatives.\n\nIn “Mastering Agile Project Management for IT Projects,” Sin Fatt equips learners with practical techniques for managing agile projects from initiation to delivery. His training covers sprint management, backlog prioritization, and agile team collaboration using tools like Jira and Trello. Through experiential learning and case-driven discussions, he helps participants master agile frameworks that foster transparency, speed, and continuous value creation in IT project environments.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta stephen tan' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Tan Khiang Meng is a seasoned data analytics and business intelligence professional with extensive experience in applying statistical methods for performance tracking and operational optimization. With a strong background in Microsoft Excel, data modeling, and visualization, he has guided organizations in using descriptive and inferential statistics to make informed decisions. Over the past two decades, he has trained professionals across industries on data literacy, reporting automation, and analytical thinking, emphasizing clarity and precision in data interpretation.\n\nIn “Statistical Data Analysis with Excel for Beginners,” Khiang Meng introduces participants to the foundational concepts of statistics through hands-on exercises using Excel. His sessions cover descriptive analysis, data visualization, and hypothesis testing, focusing on real-world applications in business and research. By simplifying complex concepts, he helps learners build confidence in applying statistical tools to uncover trends, analyze variability, and support data-driven decisions effectively.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta tan kian meng' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Terence Ee is an experienced IT leader and consultant with more than 25 years of expertise in technology management, information systems, and digital transformation. He has served as Chief Information Officer at the Supreme Court of Singapore and Vice President of Information Systems at Senoko Energy, where he led major IT modernization projects. Since 2017, he has worked as an independent consultant and ACLP-certified trainer, specializing in guiding SMEs and enterprises in adopting future-ready digital platforms.\n\nAs a WSQ-accredited trainer, Terence delivers programs in digital collaboration, IT governance, and productivity tools. His facilitation emphasizes case studies, simulations, and hands-on practice, enabling learners to apply modern IT systems such as Microsoft 365 and Google Workspace to improve collaboration and business efficiency. With his leadership background and deep IT expertise, Terence prepares learners to thrive in digitally transforming environments.\n\nTeddy Yip Fook Khi: Teddy Yip Fook Khi is a business consultant and corporate trainer with over 25 years of experience in financial management, process improvement, and digital transformation. He holds a Master of Science in Finance and Controlling and is a certified WSQ Advanced Certificate in Learning and Performance (ACLP) trainer. Teddy has delivered training in data analytics, financial modelling, and Python programming for business professionals across various industries, helping organizations modernize their workflows through technology-driven solutions. His expertise lies in combining financial analysis with automation and data-driven decision-making to enhance productivity and business insight.\n\nIn the Basic Python Programming for Financial Services course, Teddy focuses on helping learners apply Python to solve real-world financial problems such as data manipulation, forecasting, and performance analysis. His sessions emphasize hands-on coding and analytical exercises, bridging financial concepts with programming fundamentals. Learners gain the practical skills to automate reporting, analyze datasets, and improve efficiency within financial operations.\n\nNoel Lou: Noel Lou is a financial technology professional and data analytics educator with deep expertise in quantitative analysis, financial systems, and programming for business applications. He has extensive experience implementing analytics solutions and automation tools for the finance and banking sectors, leveraging Python, SQL, and Excel VBA to optimize data workflows and reporting accuracy. As an ACLP-certified trainer, Noel has designed and delivered professional courses in data analytics, programming, and digital transformation for both public and corporate clients. His ability to translate complex technical concepts into simple, practical lessons has made him a highly sought-after instructor among finance professionals.\n\nIn this course, Noel teaches learners how to apply Python programming to streamline financial operations and derive insights from data. His structured, hands-on approach helps participants build confidence in coding fundamentals, data cleaning, and visualization using libraries such as Pandas and Matplotlib. Learners complete real-world exercises that simulate financial analysis and automation tasks, equipping them with the skills to enhance data accuracy and efficiency in financial environments.\n\nDr. Alfred Ang: Dr. Alfred Ang is a veteran technology educator and entrepreneur with over 25 years of experience in IT, artificial intelligence, and financial systems. He holds a PhD in Electrical Engineering from the National University of Singapore, an MEng from NTU, and an MBA from Universitas 21 Global. As the Founder and Managing Director of Tertiary Infotech Pte. Ltd., Dr. Ang has developed and delivered numerous accredited programs in data analytics, AI, and programming for financial services. His expertise bridges academic research and industry practice, with a strong focus on the practical application of emerging technologies to enhance business intelligence and performance.\n\nIn the Basic Python Programming for Financial Services course, Dr. Ang helps learners build a solid foundation in Python for data processing, automation, and analysis. His sessions focus on the use of Python to manage datasets, perform trend analysis, and model financial outcomes. Through his structured and interactive approach, participants gain both technical proficiency and analytical insight to apply programming skills effectively in finance-related tasks and decision-making processes.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta terence ee' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Truman Ng, PMP®, HCIE®, ACTA, CBP, is a highly credentialed IT professional with extensive expertise in cloud infrastructure, networking, and enterprise systems administration. Holding advanced certifications such as Huawei HCIE®, Cisco CCNP/CCIP/CCDP, ITILv3, and PMP®, he brings a strong foundation in both system reliability and service management. With his WSQ Advanced Certificate in Training and Assessment (ACTA), Truman is well-equipped to deliver structured, outcome-driven training that aligns with WSQ standards. His background in large-scale enterprise networking, security, and cloud solutions positions him as a capable guide for learners aspiring to master Kubernetes administration at an advanced level.\n\nAs a trainer, Truman has successfully delivered courses across Docker (Basic & Advanced), CI/CD pipelines, Ansible, Python, and cybersecurity, alongside modules in cloud networking and automation. These skill areas are directly relevant to CKA training, which focuses on cluster installation, configuration, troubleshooting, and securing Kubernetes environments. His hands-on experience in containerization, orchestration, and DevOps tools enables him to bridge theory with practical application, ensuring learners build both competence and confidence. With a teaching approach that blends technical depth with clear pedagogy, Truman prepares participants to administer Kubernetes clusters effectively and achieve Certified Kubernetes Administrator certification.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'acta truman ng' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
