UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Agnes Low is an accounting and finance educator with more than 15 years of experience in corporate finance, auditing, and training. She has served in leadership roles in finance and compliance functions and has conducted workshops in business finance, cost management, and performance reporting. Her deep understanding of financial systems and regulations allows her to guide learners through both the technical and practical dimensions of financial management.\n\nIn “Accounting for Non-Finance Managers,” Agnes helps professionals develop a solid foundation in financial interpretation and analysis. Her lessons focus on demystifying accounting principles, reading financial statements, and using financial data for strategic planning and performance evaluation. By connecting accounting knowledge to real-world management scenarios, she enables participants to make informed decisions that drive organizational success and accountability.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'agnes low' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Agus Salim is an experienced IT solutions and cybersecurity professional with a strong foundation in cloud infrastructure and project management. With over a decade of experience in systems integration, software development, and IT security across both enterprise and consulting environments, he brings a practical understanding of secure system design and deployment. His credentials include PMP, CompTIA Security+, CEH, and AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner, reflecting his balanced expertise in governance, risk management, and cloud operations. Agus has worked with leading organizations such as Citi and Check Point Software Technologies, providing hands-on technical and security support across multi-cloud platforms.\n\nIn the AWS Certified Machine Learning Specialty Training course, Agus emphasizes secure cloud implementation for AI and ML systems. He trains participants to integrate security-by-design principles into AWS-based data pipelines and machine learning workflows. His sessions focus on end-to-end ML lifecycle management—from data preparation and model training to monitoring and governance—ensuring learners are equipped to deploy AI solutions that meet industry and compliance standards.\n\nAlec Tan Chee Wee: Alec Tan Chee Wee is an experienced IT trainer and systems engineer with over 20 years of professional experience in network infrastructure, systems administration, and technical support. He holds multiple CompTIA certifications including A+, Network+, and Server+, along with the WSQ Advanced Certificate in Learning and Performance (ACLP). Alec began his career in IT systems integration and sales management before founding and managing an IT retail and repair business at Sim Lim Square, later transitioning into corporate IT support and training. His technical expertise spans Microsoft Windows Server, enterprise networking, and hardware/software troubleshooting for desktop, mobile, and hybrid environments.\n\nIn the CompTIA Certified Network+ Training, Alec combines hands-on networking experience with instructional clarity to help learners build a solid foundation in network design, configuration, and troubleshooting. His sessions focus on real-world implementation scenarios involving LAN/WAN architecture, security protocols, and performance optimization. With his practical and engaging teaching style, Alec ensures participants gain both the conceptual knowledge and applied skills required to succeed as competent network professionals.\n\nDr. Alfred Ang: Dr. Alfred Ang is a distinguished technology educator, entrepreneur, and industry practitioner with over 25 years of experience in IT, AI, cybersecurity, and digital transformation. He holds a PhD in Electrical Engineering from the National University of Singapore, an MEng and MSc from NTU, and an MBA from Universitas 21 Global. As the Founder and Managing Director of Tertiary Infotech Pte Ltd, he has led the development of over 130 WSQ and IBF-accredited courses in areas such as cloud computing, cybersecurity, data analytics, and software engineering. Dr. Ang is also ACTA, DACE, and GCWLP certified, as well as an IBM-certified AI Practitioner and Microsoft Azure Fundamentals credential holder.\n\nIn the CompTIA Certified Network+ Training, Dr. Ang integrates his deep technical expertise and adult education experience to deliver comprehensive instruction on modern network technologies. His approach blends academic rigor with hands-on application, guiding learners through key networking concepts, protocols, and troubleshooting methodologies. With a focus on industry relevance and employability, Dr. Ang empowers participants to apply networking principles effectively in real-world IT environments.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'agus salim' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
