eadership and communication coach with over two decades of corporate experience in business development, project management, and client relations. He has facilitated workshops in communication strategies, conflict resolution, and team collaboration for both corporate and government clients. Teddy’s expertise lies in helping professionals build stronger interpersonal connections and navigate challenging conversations in high-stakes environments.\n\nIn “Mastering the Art of Communication to Enhance Team Collaboration and Customer Satisfaction,” Teddy guides participants in developing communication agility and emotional awareness to foster teamwork and customer trust. His sessions focus on persuasive communication, cross-functional collaboration, and effective feedback techniques. Drawing from his leadership experience, he empowers learners to build authentic relationships that strengthen team synergy and customer loyalty.\n\nAllen Wong: Allen Wong is a multimedia designer and educator with extensive experience in creative communication, digital storytelling, and training design. Having worked in both creative industries and professional development environments, he specializes in helping individuals and organizations communicate ideas visually and effectively. His expertise bridges design, communication, and technology—enabling participants to express messages with clarity, impact, and engagement.\n\nIn “Mastering the Art of Communication to Enhance Team Collaboration and Customer Satisfaction,” Allen applies creative communication techniques to enhance collaboration and service delivery. His sessions blend visual communication principles with interpersonal skills, teaching participants how to convey ideas confidently and align team goals. By integrating storytelling and empathy-driven communication, he helps professionals strengthen collaboration and deliver meaningful, customer-centered interactions.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'armand abdul rahim' AND (description 