UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Janice Ong is an experienced marketing strategist, business development professional, and WSQ-certified ACLP trainer with over 20 years of experience across IT, engineering, and e-commerce sectors. Having led regional marketing and sales operations for Creative Technology, Asco Freight, and Condat, she has a strong foundation in digital strategy, brand communications, and international business expansion. As a freelance digital marketing consultant and trainer since 2014, she has mentored professionals and business owners in SEO, SEM, and online brand development across multiple CMS and e-commerce platforms such as Shopify and WooCommerce.\n\nIn “Create Engaging Social E-Commerce Campaigns on XiaoHongShu,” Janice guides participants through the end-to-end process of building compelling brand narratives and optimizing social selling strategies. Her lessons focus on content marketing, platform analytics, and influencer collaboration—empowering learners to create authentic and high-performing XiaoHongShu campaigns that resonate with China’s digitally savvy consumer base.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'janice ong hui li' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = '- Jasmine Sho is an experienced trainer and facilitator specializing in workplace communication, team effectiveness, and leadership development. With a career in both corporate and adult training, she has designed and delivered programs on negotiation, conflict management, and interpersonal communication for SMEs and multinational organizations. Her facilitation style is highly interactive, focusing on building confidence and collaboration among learners.\n\nIn this course, Jasmine equips participants with practical tools to manage and resolve conflicts constructively. She emphasizes techniques such as reframing, mediation, and collaborative dialogue to transform conflict into opportunities for growth. By focusing on both individual and team perspectives, Jasmine ensures learners walk away with the ability to manage tensions productively and strengthen collaboration within their workplace.\n\nGary Chan Kim Heng: Gary Chan Kim Heng is a Chartered Accountant (Singapore) with over 25 years of senior management and corporate finance experience across multinational and local organizations. A former Regional CFO and Vice President (Asia Pacific) for a Fortune 500 company, Gary has led financial strategy, corporate planning, and business transformation initiatives in diverse industries. He holds an MBA from Brunel University (UK), an MSc in Strategic Marketing from the National University of Ireland, and is a certified ACCA member. As Founder and Principal Trainer at Smart Skill Training & Consulting, he has conducted numerous workshops for corporate and public institutions on accounting, corporate finance, and strategic management.\n\nIn the Tax Computations for Individuals and Organizations course, Gary integrates his deep industry background with a practical teaching approach to help learners understand Singapore’s tax framework, computation methodologies, and compliance requirements. His sessions emphasize real-world application of taxation principles for financial planning, business decision-making, and organizational sustainability.\n\nBell Ang Chai Huat: Bell Ang Chai Huat is a seasoned finance and IT professional with over 45 years of experience in accounting, auditing, and enterprise system implementation. A Certified Public Accountant (CPA Singapore) and CPA Australia member, she has held senior roles such as Finance and HR Manager at Torishima Service Solutions and Regional Finance Manager at BJ Services Company. Her expertise spans financial reporting, GST compliance, internal control design, and accounting software implementation including Oracle ERP, Hyperion, and MYOB. She also holds the WSQ Advanced Certificate in Training and Assessment (ACTA).\n\nIn this taxation course, Bell combines her extensive financial management experience with her deep understanding of accounting systems to deliver comprehensive insights on tax reporting and compliance. She helps learners build practical skills in tax computation for individuals and organizations, emphasizing accuracy, audit preparedness, and effective use of financial tools for tax planning and corporate governance.\n\nMalcolm Soo Chee Kong: Malcolm Soo Chee Kong is an experienced finance professional and Chartered Accountant of Singapore with a strong background in financial planning, analysis, and reporting. Over his career with organizations such as JTC Corporation and Sumitomo Electric Wintec, he has managed financial policies, tax computations, budgeting, and audit compliance for multi-million-dollar projects. As a trainer and lecturer, Malcolm has delivered accounting and financial management courses including LCCI Level 1 & 2 and Accounting for Non-Financial Professionals, bringing practical corporate insights into the classroom.\n\nIn the Tax Computations for Individuals and Organizations course, Malcolm leverages his hands-on experience in financial reporting and compliance to teach learners how to prepare, review, and validate tax computations in line with Singapore’s IRAS guidelines. His instruction emphasizes analytical thinking, compliance accuracy, and the integration of tax planning into overall business strategy, preparing participants to manage taxation processes confidently and efficiently.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'jasmine sho choon kim' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Jazreel Ari is an image maker/art director/graphic designer who had her recent work exhibited at Alliance Francaise Singapore. She graduated from Lasalle College of the Arts (Goldsmith College, University of London) with a BA(Hons) in Design Communication. “Around here we don\'t look backwards for very long. We keep moving forward, opening up new doors and doing new things, because we\'re curious and curiosity keeps leading us down new paths.” — Walt Disney' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'jazreel ari' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Jim Gan Chiu Liang is an experienced software developer and data automation specialist with over 15 years of experience in designing and implementing Microsoft Excel VBA solutions for business process optimization. His expertise lies in developing automated workflows, interactive dashboards, and complex financial models that reduce manual workload and improve data accuracy. Jim has worked with organizations across finance, logistics, and education sectors, helping them leverage Excel’s advanced programming capabilities to drive efficiency and decision-making.\n\nIn “Software Automation with Excel VBA Programming,” Jim focuses on teaching participants how to use VBA to automate repetitive tasks, manage large datasets, and build dynamic business applications. His sessions emphasize practical project development—ranging from macro creation to custom form design—enabling learners to translate business logic into efficient, maintainable code. By combining hands-on exercises with real-world case studies, he empowers professionals to build powerful, automated Excel solutions.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'jim gan chiu liang' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
