UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Jyoti Chopra is an experienced AutoCAD instructor and design professional with extensive expertise in architectural design, furniture design, simulation, and 3D visualization. She has worked on projects involving technical drawing, space planning, and digital prototyping, helping learners and organizations develop skills in design documentation and visualization. Her teaching is grounded in industry-relevant experience, ensuring participants acquire both creativity and technical proficiency.\n\nAs a trainer, Jyoti has taught WSQ and professional courses in AutoCAD, graphic design, and 3D modeling, emphasizing practical application and portfolio-ready outputs. She leverages real-world case studies and design projects to help learners master AutoCAD tools and apply them to diverse industries. Her facilitation style encourages creativity, precision, and efficiency, enabling participants to confidently use design software for both academic and professional growth.\n\nDr. Alfred Ang: Dr. Alfred Ang is a distinguished technology educator, researcher, and entrepreneur with more than 25 years of experience across IT, AI, and software development. He holds a PhD in Electrical Engineering from the National University of Singapore, an MEng from NTU, and an MBA from Universitas 21 Global. As the Founder and Managing Director of Tertiary Infotech Pte. Ltd., Dr. Ang has led the design and development of over 130 WSQ- and IBF-accredited courses spanning data analytics, cloud computing, and digital transformation. His technical background includes software engineering, programming, and emerging technologies such as extended reality (XR) and AI for creative industries.\n\nIn the Fast-Track to Unreal Game Development course, Dr. Ang combines his expertise in software architecture and technical education to provide learners with a strong foundation in Unreal Engine and interactive media systems. His sessions emphasize structured development workflows, coding fundamentals, and creative problem-solving techniques essential to modern game production. Through his guidance, participants gain both the technical competence and strategic mindset to succeed in the fast-evolving field of game design and development.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'jyoti chopra' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
