UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Kesston Tang is a seasoned consultant and trainer with expertise in business negotiations, financial analysis, and corporate advisory services. He has developed consulting frameworks that support organizations in improving negotiation outcomes, optimizing business deals, and managing stakeholder relations. His clients include major corporations and government agencies, where he has provided advisory services in both local and international contexts.\n\nIn this WSQ program, Kesston brings his business consulting and negotiation experience to guide learners in applying strategic negotiation techniques. His training focuses on balancing tactical approaches with relationship management, ensuring participants leave with the ability to negotiate effectively and unlock sustainable value for their organizations.\n\nTerence Ee: Terence Ee is a business consultant and corporate trainer with over 20 years of experience in management, process improvement, and strategic communication. He has led high-level projects across industries including technology, manufacturing, and professional services, specializing in leadership development, quality management, and stakeholder engagement. As a certified adult educator, Terence combines analytical problem-solving with practical communication strategies to help professionals build influence and achieve organizational alignment.\n\nIn “Unlocking Business Potential with Strategic Negotiation Tactics,” Terence focuses on developing the negotiation mindset and interpersonal agility needed to achieve win-win outcomes. His sessions emphasize structured negotiation frameworks, emotional intelligence, and cross-cultural communication in business contexts. Through role plays and real-world case studies, he equips participants with proven strategies to strengthen client relationships, resolve conflicts, and drive successful outcomes in complex business negotiations.\n\nTeddy Yip Fook Khin: Teddy Yip is a leadership and communication coach with more than two decades of experience in business development, client relations, and organizational transformation. Having worked with multinational corporations and educational institutions, he has facilitated numerous training programs in negotiation, persuasion, and interpersonal effectiveness. His ability to simplify complex communication dynamics allows participants to understand and apply negotiation principles with confidence and clarity.\n\nIn “Unlocking Business Potential with Strategic Negotiation Tactics,” Teddy guides learners through the art and psychology of effective negotiation. His sessions focus on mastering communication techniques, building trust, and creating collaborative solutions that strengthen business partnerships. By blending theory with experiential learning, he empowers professionals to negotiate with confidence, adaptability, and strategic intent—enhancing both personal and organizational success.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'kesston tang' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Khoo Yong is an ACTA-certified trainer with a strong foundation in adult education and applied analytics. With years of experience in training and mentoring learners, he specializes in simplifying complex concepts in data analysis and statistical methods for beginners. His expertise includes guiding participants in applying R programming to perform descriptive statistics, hypothesis testing, and data visualization, equipping them with practical skills to analyze data effectively and interpret results with confidence.\n\nAs a certified adult educator, Khoo Yong ensures his training is engaging, structured, and accessible to learners from diverse backgrounds. He emphasizes hands-on practice with R, enabling participants to bridge theory with application in real-world contexts. His learner-centered approach not only builds technical competency but also fosters analytical thinking, preparing participants to use statistical tools in business, research, and decision-making.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'khoo yong' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Kishori Chaudhari is an accomplished educator, trainer, and communication specialist with extensive experience in developing and delivering customer-focused learning solutions. Holding a Master of Arts in TESOL, a Bachelor’s degree in Speech and Language Therapy from the University of Manchester, and multiple professional certifications including the WSQ Advanced Certificate in Learning and Performance (ACLP) and the WSQ Diploma in Design and Development of Learning for Performance (DDDLP), Kishori brings a strong foundation in adult learning and communication sciences. Her career spans roles as a learning solutionist, assessor for SSG-funded certifiable courses, and trainer across diverse sectors, where she has supported enterprises navigating transformation by aligning communication strategies with performance needs.\n\nBeyond her academic and training expertise, Kishori has cultivated a rich professional background in service excellence, branding, and customer engagement. Her career highlights include experience as a leading stewardess with Singapore Airlines, where she honed skills in premium customer service, as well as a background in the food and beverage industry as a sous chef at Rang Mahal, where she oversaw quality, consistency, and customer satisfaction. Combined with her certifications in speech, drama, and communication from prestigious institutions such as the London Academy of Music and Dramatic Arts (LAMDA) and the London College of Music (LCM), she integrates creativity, empathy, and practical techniques into her training. Kishori’s unique blend of communication expertise, service excellence, and adult training pedagogy positions her to guide learners in mastering customer-centric branding and communication tactics that build trust, enhance brand value, and strengthen customer relationships' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'kishori chaudhari' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'James Lee is an Adobe Certified Expert and ACLP-certified trainer with over 20 years of experience in training, digital media, and web development. He has served as Chief Instructor at ACE Training, adjunct lecturer at Singapore Polytechnic, and trainer for corporations and universities across the region. His expertise includes Adobe Illustrator, Photoshop, InDesign, and web technologies, alongside certifications in digital marketing and content strategy.\n\nIn his Illustrator training, James focuses on practical applications of vector graphics in branding, publishing, and digital media. His sessions cover Illustrator’s essential tools, creative workflows, and project-based learning, ensuring learners develop industry-relevant design skills. With his blend of technical mastery and extensive teaching experience, James empowers participants to create professional-grade illustrations and designs confidently.\n\nLeong Jin Jie (JJ): Leong Jin Jie, also known as JJ, is a multidisciplinary designer and digital media specialist with extensive experience in photo editing, visual storytelling, and creative design. With a strong foundation in Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator, and Lightroom, he has worked on projects spanning branding, advertising, and digital content production. JJ’s creative expertise lies in transforming raw visuals into striking, professional-grade imagery through precision editing, retouching, and compositional balance. His work reflects a blend of technical mastery and artistic vision, empowering learners to approach digital imaging with both creativity and purpose.\n\nIn “Professional Digital Image Editing with Photoshop,” JJ focuses on building learners’ proficiency in advanced image manipulation, color correction, and non-destructive editing workflows. His sessions emphasize practical techniques for enhancing photos, creating composite images, and preparing assets for web and print media. Through guided, hands-on exercises, he helps participants gain confidence in using Photoshop’s powerful tools to produce polished, high-impact visuals that align with professional design standards.\n\nMatthew Tan: Matthew Tan is a creative designer and multimedia artist with a strong background in digital imaging, visual communication, and post-production design. Proficient in Adobe Photoshop and Creative Cloud applications, he has developed numerous projects in advertising, branding, and digital content creation. His design philosophy integrates aesthetics with precision editing, ensuring visuals that are both visually captivating and technically sound. Matthew’s industry experience allows him to teach Photoshop not just as a tool but as a creative medium for professional design expression.\n\nIn “Professional Digital Image Editing with Photoshop,” Matthew guides learners through essential and advanced photo editing techniques used in professional design workflows. His lessons include image restoration, retouching, adjustment layers, and compositing for creative effects. By focusing on hands-on application and artistic direction, he equips participants with the skills to produce refined, high-quality imagery that meets commercial and creative standards.\n\nThomas Yeo: Thomas Yeo is a seasoned visual designer, photographer, and digital content creator with over a decade of experience in creative design and media production. His expertise in Adobe Photoshop, combined with a strong background in visual aesthetics and photographic composition, enables him to produce impactful visual narratives. Thomas has worked on diverse creative projects, ranging from advertising and corporate communications to fine-art photography, making him adept at bridging artistry with technical execution.\n\nIn “Professional Digital Image Editing with Photoshop,” Thomas focuses on helping learners master Photoshop’s advanced tools for photo manipulation, color grading, and artistic enhancement. His sessions emphasize visual balance, lighting correction, and digital retouching, enabling participants to transform raw images into professionally polished works. Through a project-based learning approach, Thomas ensures that learners not only understand the technical aspects of Photoshop but also develop a creative eye for producing compelling and visually consistent designs.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'lee kin nam james' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Leon Ye Jin Hong is a ACTA certified trainer.  He have exprience in RPA Architect, Test Automation lead, Coach and Trainer, Cloud Engineer(Azure) and Data Analysis. The Automation solutions have benefited Land Transport Authority, MINDEF Singapore, Ministry of Education(MOE), Ministry of Development(MND) Singapore Press Holdings(sph),ST Engineering, Accenture, Defence Science & Technology Agency(DSTA) and Singapore Exchange. Some Robotic Process Automation that he experience in: Automated Booking System(Customer Service), Finance Invoice Processing, HR Recruitment, HR onboarding & Offboarding and Automated Data Exchange & Reporting Generation.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'leon ye jin hong' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Leong Jin Jie, also known as JJ, is a multidisciplinary designer and creative technologist specializing in user interface (UI) and user experience (UX) design for both web and mobile platforms. With a strong background in digital product design, prototyping, and front-end implementation, JJ has worked with startups and established enterprises to create intuitive, high-performing digital interfaces. His expertise spans across tools such as Figma, Adobe XD, and Webflow, where he integrates visual design principles with interaction logic to craft user-centered digital experiences. As an educator and design mentor, JJ has guided aspiring designers in mastering visual hierarchy, responsive design, and usability best practices.\n\nIn “Mastering UI Design Techniques for Web and Mobile,” JJ helps learners develop the creative and technical skills necessary to design modern, engaging interfaces that balance aesthetics and functionality. His sessions focus on grid systems, typography, color theory, and prototyping workflows while introducing accessibility and design system principles. Through hands-on projects, JJ empowers participants to translate design concepts into interactive, professional-grade UI mockups suitable for both web and mobile environments.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'leong jin jie (jj)' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Liew Sing Loon is a ACTA certified trainer. Liew Sing Loon graduated from the National University of Singapore (NUS) in 1992 with a Second Upper Honors Degree in Electrical Engineering. He started his career as an Electronic Product Design Engineer for four years in a Multinational Company which sell the products worldwide. The job provided him practical knowledge in various aspects of manufacturing operations ranges from Design, Quality, Production and Procurement. He then spent fifteen years in Information Technology Sector as a Key Account Manager in selling IT solutions to Banking, Telecommunications and Government clients. The job provided him the opportunities to propose IT solutions, integrating software, hardware and services, to solve customers’ problems to achieve their strategic business objectives. He joint a German Product Test company to develop its business in providing product Safety, Immunity, Electromagnetic Compatibility (EMC) Certification test. While working in the industry, Liew Sing Loon obtained a Master of Science (MSc) in Technology Management from NUS.\n\nIn the last decade, Liew Sing Loon has been Adjunct Lecturer in several Institutes of high learning, transferring his knowledge on Quantitative &amp; Statistical Analysis, Operations, Project &amp; Quality Management to learners ranging from Diploma, full time undergraduates and working adults.Liew Sing Loon has a Certificate of Completion in Education Psychology Course and Teaching & Learning in Higher Education Program conducted by National Institute of Education (NIE).' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'liew seng loon' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Liew Sing Loon (Sen Ru) is an IT systems specialist and data analytics educator with extensive experience in software automation and database integration. With a strong background in programming and information management, he has trained professionals in applying Excel VBA and SQL to solve complex business challenges. His expertise in workflow design and automation enables organizations to modernize their reporting systems and streamline data processing.\n\nIn “Software Automation with Excel VBA Programming,” Sing Loon focuses on building a strong foundation in coding logic and automation best practices. His sessions emphasize modular programming, user interface design, and efficient data handling in Excel environments. Through structured exercises and case-based learning, he equips learners with the skills to build, test, and deploy automated tools that improve business efficiency and data accuracy.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'liew sing loon (sen ru)' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = '– Lim Cheng Chong is an ACTA-certified trainer and NUS Computer Science graduate with a focus on education and interactive media. He has over 5 years of classroom teaching experience at institutions such as BCA Academy and NUS, in addition to creating more than 900 educational videos with over 5 million views on his YouTube channel. His expertise includes web programming, app development, IoT, and applied machine learning, supported by professional training engagements with CSIT, SMRT, Panasonic, HP, and other organizations.\n\nIn his React training, Cheng Chong leverages his extensive teaching and content creation experience to simplify complex coding concepts for beginners. His sessions emphasize hands-on learning, guiding participants through building functional React applications while reinforcing programming fundamentals. With his proven track record in both education and real-world projects, he equips learners to confidently develop and deploy their first web apps using React.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'lim cheng chong' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Lim Fang Cheng Fritz is a software developer and computing educator specializing in C# programming, software engineering, and game development. With strong expertise in Unity and .NET frameworks, he has designed and delivered numerous training programs that emphasize structured programming, algorithmic problem-solving, and clean coding practices. His teaching approach bridges theory with practical application, enabling learners to gain confidence in coding, debugging, and system design for both educational and industrial contexts.\n\nIn “Programming Methodologies in C#,” Fritz focuses on guiding participants through the design, implementation, and optimization of object-oriented applications. His sessions emphasize modular architecture, debugging best practices, and the application of C# in modern software ecosystems. Through hands-on projects, he helps participants master the principles of maintainable code and structured logic that underpin robust application development.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'lim fang cheng, fritz' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Noel Lou is an experienced embedded systems engineer and educator with over 15 years of expertise in C programming, IoT development, and robotics integration. He has designed and implemented numerous automation projects using Arduino, Raspberry Pi, and ESP32 platforms for both industrial and educational applications. As an ACLP-certified trainer, Noel is known for his ability to simplify complex programming and hardware integration concepts, making them accessible to learners from diverse technical backgrounds. His passion for teaching lies in bridging electronics, coding, and AI-assisted design to foster innovation and creativity.\n\nIn “AI-Assisted C Programming for Arduino,” Noel teaches participants how to leverage generative AI tools to accelerate embedded software development and hardware prototyping. His sessions focus on AI-guided code generation, debugging, and optimization techniques to streamline C programming workflows. Through hands-on exercises involving real-world Arduino projects, he equips learners with the skills to design intelligent systems that blend classical programming with modern AI-driven development approaches.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'lou yong liang, noel' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Chee Tat started his first job in startup - AMS. That\'s where he sharpened his skills in Full-stack Java Web Development, Software Design, and soft skills such as requirements gathering with client, client-handling during UAT, client training and \"how to drive in and out from Singapore\". 8 months later, AMS decided to promote Chee Tat as Team Lead after seeing his leadership potential. 4 years later, Chee Tat joined IBM via the headhunter. Started as an individual contributor, Chee Tat was playing around with many IBM Middleware/SOA products such as MQ, WMB and etc. Chee Tat also designed and built many Java programs combined with other IBM Middleware products as interfaces to the clients\' legacy systems. 1 year later he was promoted as SOA Adapter Team Lead to lead 3-5 developers. Chee Tat\'s won 3 awards during his service with IBM.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'low chee tat' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
