UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Malcolm Soo is an ACTA-certified trainer and Chartered Accountant of Singapore with more than 20 years of professional experience in accounting, financial planning, and internal control compliance. His career includes senior roles at JTC Corporation and Eu Yan Sang, where he was responsible for financial reporting, budgeting, and system integration. He has delivered training in LCCI accounting modules and corporate programs on financial systems, focusing on bridging technical accounting knowledge with practical business applications.\n\nIn his training for SMEs, Malcolm specializes in helping participants understand the integration of accounting and tax systems with financial management processes. His sessions cover account setup, tax reporting, receivables and payables management, and compliance frameworks. With his strong accounting and training background, he equips learners to leverage accounting systems effectively to improve business transparency and financial governance.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'malcolm soo chee kong' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Mamun Abdul Mannan is a coder, designer, teacher and incurable travel lover. He is passionate by the intersection of code and design. His aim is to provide simple, intelligent and emotionally appealing solutions to complex requirements in the field of Professional in Corporate Branding, Graphic designing, Logos, Brochures, Posters, Banner, Web designing, Web developing, Web Application and so on.\n\nAlan Wong is an awards winning (MVA Awards) professional 3D animation director, film director, video editor, creative design and a passionate tutor who like to share his 25 years of valuable hand on Experiences in creative field to all students who keen to improve their skills for better income and career advancement by learning his legacy of secret tips and technical knowledge.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'mamun abdul mannan' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = '– Marcel Leng is an ICT professional and educator with strong expertise in machine learning, cryptography, and applied mathematics. He has conducted extensive research and training in AI, data science, and quantum algorithms, and has guided learners in applying advanced computational tools to real-world security challenges.\n\nFor this WSQ course, Marcel focuses on the technical aspects of quantum algorithms, quantum-safe encryption, and cryptographic resilience. His sessions emphasize hands-on demonstrations, case studies, and applied problem-solving, equipping learners with the ability to analyze, design, and implement secure systems in anticipation of quantum advancements.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'marcel leng' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Mark Tan Kee Tchuan is a Lean Six Sigma Master Black Belt practitioner with over 20 years of experience in organizational transformation and operational process improvement. He specializes in leveraging Lean and Six Sigma methodologies to optimize both operational and transactional environments, leading cross-functional projects to drive standardization, efficiency, and business outcomes. Mark has successfully implemented process redesign and resource optimization strategies, delivering measurable improvements across various sectors including logistics, manufacturing, service, and healthcare.\n\nWith 6 years of industry consulting experience, Mark has built a strong business network through successful project delivery. He is also a Certified Scrum Master with over a decade of project management experience, overseeing large-scale system implementations, benchmarking, and cost optimization initiatives. Passionate about digitalization and automation, Mark has led RPA projects and applied design thinking to enhance user experience. His recent focus includes HR and enterprise-wide process re-engineering, where he leads continuous improvement initiatives and trains professionals in Lean Six Sigma. In addition, he has been an adjunct faculty member at Singapore Institute of Technology (SIT) since 2016, certifying Yellow Belt students in continuous improvement.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'mark tan kee tchuan' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Matthew Tan is a technology trainer and computer science graduate with deep expertise in C++, C#, ASP.NET, and secure systems development. Holding a Bachelor of Computer Science (Digital Systems Security) from the University of Wollongong, he has conducted training for Ministry of Education (MOE) schools and private centers across Singapore, covering topics such as coding, design thinking, and robotics. His experience spans teaching at renowned schools including Chung Cheng High, Anglican High, and Singapore Chinese Girls’ School, where his students have achieved national-level awards for research, presentation, and robot design.\n\nIn “Programming Methodologies in C#,” Matthew applies his software engineering and cybersecurity background to teach structured programming principles in real-world contexts. His lessons emphasize algorithmic problem-solving, debugging, and the application of object-oriented design in C#. Drawing from both his training and development experience, he helps learners translate core programming theory into practical, high-performance code aligned with industry best practices.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'matthew tan' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Milton Sim is an experienced DevOps engineer and cloud computing specialist with more than 17 years of expertise in system integration, automation, and infrastructure management. He has worked with organizations to design and deploy cloud-native applications using Kubernetes, Docker, and CI/CD pipelines. As a certified Kubernetes professional and ACLP-qualified trainer, Milton is dedicated to helping learners master container orchestration technologies through structured, hands-on instruction.\n\nIn “Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA) Training (Synchronous e-Learning),” Milton focuses on the operational aspects of Kubernetes administration, including cluster configuration, resource management, and service networking. His sessions emphasize automation, scaling, and monitoring of containerized workloads. Through real-world use cases and practical labs, he enables participants to gain the confidence and technical skills needed to deploy and manage Kubernetes clusters efficiently.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'milton sim' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Shanique is an ACLP-certified trainer and design professional with more than a decade of experience in visual communication, digital media, and adult learning. She holds a Diploma in Visual Communication from First Media Academy and a Certificate in UX/UI from LASALLE College of the Arts, along with multiple WSQ certifications in design software including Adobe Photoshop. She has trained adult learners under WSQ programs at institutions such as Tertiary Infotech and First Media Academy, specializing in Photoshop, Illustrator, and InDesign.\n\nIn her Photoshop courses, Shanique emphasizes practical, hands-on training that makes digital image editing accessible for beginners and professionals alike. Her sessions cover core Photoshop techniques including retouching, adjustments, layers, masks, and effects, while also exploring design workflows for branding and publication. With her strong background in both design and training, she empowers learners to confidently produce polished, professional images for business and creative use.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'moh pei lan (shanique)' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
UPDATE courses_trainers SET description = 'Mohamed Afiq is a Python developer and data analytics professional specializing in web development, API design, and automation. With experience in both frontend and backend programming, he has built RESTful APIs and Flask-based applications for data visualization, reporting, and integration with cloud services. Afiq’s technical expertise spans Python, SQL, Flask, and JavaScript, alongside modern deployment tools such as Docker and Git. As an educator, he focuses on hands-on learning and practical implementation, guiding learners from foundational programming concepts to building full-stack web applications.\n\nIn “Create RESTful APIs and Web Apps with Python Flask,” Afiq teaches participants how to design, develop, and deploy dynamic web applications using Python. His sessions cover essential Flask components such as routing, templating, and database integration, with a strong focus on REST API best practices and JSON-based communication. Through real-world coding exercises, he helps learners understand how to create efficient, modular, and scalable Flask applications suitable for data-driven and enterprise use cases.' WHERE LOWER(TRIM(title)) = 'mohamed afiq bin mohamed ismail' AND (description IS NULL OR description = '');
